div.p:
               England is a Priſon; the variety of ſubtilties in the Laws
preſerved by the Sword, are bolts, bars, and doors of the priſon;
the Lawyers are the Jaylors, and poor men are the priſoners;
for let a man fall into the hands of any from the Bailiffe
to the Judge, and he is either undone, or wearie of
his life.
